Name: pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma
Definition: A pancreatic adenocarcinoma that derives_from pancreatic duct cells.

Name: pancreatic cystadenocarcinoma
Definition: A gastrointestinal tuberculosis that involves infection located_in liver

Name: pancreatic acinar cell adenocarcinoma
Definition: A pancreatic adenocarcinoma that has_material_basis_in cells with morphological resemblance to acinar cells and is associated with increased serum lipase.

Name: pancreatic foamy gland adenocarcinoma
Definition: A vulva carcinoma that derives_from sweat glands and is characterized by the presence of clear cells.
